<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-62-1097 </DOCNO><TEXT>A self mode-locked laser system is described comprising: a semiconductorlaser diode having a first facet and a second facet, optical radiationbeing emitted from the second facet when the diode is driven; an opticalsystem disposed to reflect at least a portion of the optical radiationback into the diode thereby inducing self-coupling in the lase to generatean oscillating light pulse; and an electronic gain means coupled to thelaser for controlling the oscillating light pulse in the laser to producesustained steady-state oscillation, thereby made locking the laser.</TEXT></DOC>